  ],
  "text": "The canonical patterns for deploying services in Kubernetes are documented across multiple repositories:\n\n1. **API Type Definition (Authoritative Source)**: The `Deployment` struct is defined in the kubernetes/api repository at `github.com/sg-evals/api--v0.32.0` in the file `apps/v1/types.go` (line 359). This is the canonical v1 API version that is stable and recommended for production use. The same definition also exists in the main Kubernetes repository at `github.com/sg-evals/kubernetes--v1.32.0` in `staging/src/k8s.io/api/apps/v1/types.go` (line 359).\n\nThe Deployment struct contains:\n- `TypeMeta`: Kind and API version metadata\n- `ObjectMeta`: Standard Kubernetes object metadata (name, namespace, labels, annotations)\n- `Spec`: DeploymentSpec containing the desired state (replicas, selector, pod template, strategy)\n- `Status`: DeploymentStatus containing observed state information\n\n2. **Client-Side Code Pattern (Canonical Example)**: The kubernetes/client-go repository at `github.com/sg-evals/client-go--v0.32.0` provides the official client library example in `examples/create-update-delete-deployment/main.go` (starting at line 65). This demonstrates the fundamental workflow for creating, updating, and deleting Deployments programmatically.\n\nThe canonical pattern shows:\n- Building a Kubernetes client configuration from kubeconfig\n- Creating a typed clientset via `kubernetes.NewForConfig(config)`\n- Accessing the Deployments API via `clientset.AppsV1().Deployments(namespace)`\n- Constructing a Deployment object with ObjectMeta and DeploymentSpec\n- Using CRUD operations: Create(), Get(), Update(), List(), Delete()\n- Implementing retry logic for updates to handle conflicts (recommended pattern)\n\n3. **Developer Documentation**: The primary documentation sources are:\n- The client-go README at `github.com/sg-evals/client-go--v0.32.0/README.md` provides overview of the client library structure, versioning, and usage guidelines\n- The example-specific README at `github.com/sg-evals/client-go--v0.32.0/examples/create-update-delete-deployment/README.md` documents the deployment workflow with step-by-step instructions\n- The example YAML manifest at `github.com/sg-evals/kubernetes--v1.32.0/test/e2e/testing-manifests/guestbook/redis-slave-deployment.yaml.in` shows the declarative YAML format for Deployment resources\n\nThe deployment workflow documented across these repos demonstrates that Kubernetes deployments enable declarative, rolling updates for Pod and ReplicaSet management. The pattern is consistent: define the desired state in a Deployment manifest, use the client library to apply it to the cluster, and rely on the deployment controller to manage the lifecycle."
}

